        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 24 at 7:18PM EDT by NWS Binghamton NY</headline>
        <description>At 717 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms over Erin, or 11 miles southeast of Odessa, moving
northeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Ithaca, Elmira, Newfield, Danby, Caroline, Erin, Dryden, Berkshire,
Richford, and Harford.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Heavy rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
